1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,640
and be looking at verses 12 through 14 this morning.

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:06,059
As we look at these verses of scripture,

3
00:00:06,059 --> 00:00:09,140
we find that there are three distinct groups of people

4
00:00:09,140 --> 00:00:12,220
that are addressed in these three verses.

5
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:13,979
And I believe that each group mentioned

6
00:00:13,979 --> 00:00:18,260
represents a stage of spiritual growth or maturity,

7
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:20,000
and we'll see that as we go through

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,379
the passage of scripture this morning.

9
00:00:23,379 --> 00:00:26,780
Of interest to me is the fact that the individual reader,

10
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:30,600
the original recipients, the individual reader

11
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,939
from the time of its writing until this morning,

12
00:00:33,939 --> 00:00:36,700
as we would read this passage of scripture,

13
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:39,799
the individual reader will have the responsibility

14
00:00:39,799 --> 00:00:44,380
of examining and evaluating their own walk with God

15
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:47,740
to determine their own spiritual maturity

16
00:00:47,740 --> 00:00:50,819
in order to find which group you fit in.

17
00:00:50,819 --> 00:00:54,540
And I think that's of interest because the reality

18
00:00:54,540 --> 00:00:57,060
is that God has given us in this book,

19
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:59,700
as we've already made note in the past few weeks,

20
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:02,900
some tests that are to be self-administered.

21
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,019
How do you know that you know him?

22
00:01:05,019 --> 00:01:06,180
According to verse number three,

23
00:01:06,180 --> 00:01:07,940
if we keep his commandments.

24
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:10,099
How do you know if you're walking in the light?

25
00:01:10,099 --> 00:01:12,639
According to our passage that we looked at

26
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:15,639
last Sunday morning, he that loveth his brother,

27
00:01:15,639 --> 00:01:19,300
according to verse number 10, abideth in the light.

28
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:22,120
And so we can say that we know him,

29
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:25,720
but the reality is that there's some evidence, some proof.

30
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:29,220
There's that internal work that the Holy Spirit of God

31
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:33,760
does within his children, but that internal work

32
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,260
is to be evidenced on the external.

33
00:01:36,260 --> 00:01:39,040
We find that we can say that we walk in the light.

34
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,300
Our theme, walking in the light.

35
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:44,160
We know that verse number seven of 1 John 1,

36
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:47,319
if we walk in the light, as he is in the light,

37
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:51,959
the Bible would reveal to us and teach to us

38
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,319
that yes, we have fellowship with him,

39
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:56,080
but the emphasis in verse number seven

40
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,400
is that we have fellowship one with another.

41
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:03,099
And that brotherly Christian fellowship that we enjoy

42
00:02:03,099 --> 00:02:06,080
as we walk in the light, as he is in the light.

43
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:09,479
And then he says, if you think you wanna walk in the light,

44
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:11,520
if you're gonna follow this admonition,

45
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:15,000
here's how you can know a test that you can self-administer.

46
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,339
If you are loving your brother,

47
00:02:17,339 --> 00:02:19,520
then you're abiding in the light.

48
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,919
He says, if you hate your brother,

49
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:24,000
that you're walking in darkness.

50
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,020
And so we find that he's given us some of these tests.

51
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:30,240
As we come to these three verses of scripture this morning,

52
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,360
we find that he's now providing us

53
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,759
with these three groups of people that are addressed.

54
00:02:35,759 --> 00:02:37,399
And I would say this, as we think about

55
00:02:37,399 --> 00:02:40,679
our spiritual maturity and our spiritual growth,

56
00:02:40,679 --> 00:02:44,440
we know and we understand the stages

57
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:47,160
of physical growth and maturity.

58
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:50,720
In fact, I remember when our children were born

59
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:53,160
and after they were born,

60
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,880
you would take them to the doctors

61
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:57,440
and you would have some of these wellness checkups

62
00:02:57,440 --> 00:03:00,600
and you'd have these exams and you would go through

63
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:03,279
and they would measure and they would determine

64
00:03:03,279 --> 00:03:06,919
based on height and weight, the particular charts.

65
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:09,880
And there are some charts that have been developed

66
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,320
that really I would refer to

67
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,720
as being standardized growth charts.

68
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:16,759
And as you would look at the development

69
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:19,460
and growth physically speaking,

70
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:22,860
we would say that your child is above average

71
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:27,580
or your child's on average and you can gauge and monitor

72
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:31,539
and evaluate their physical growth.

73
00:03:31,539 --> 00:03:34,360
And we understand that if there is no physical growth,

74
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,119
that represents a problem.

75
00:03:36,119 --> 00:03:39,619
It gives parents a concern if there's no growth,

76
00:03:39,619 --> 00:03:41,220
if there's no development.

77
00:03:41,220 --> 00:03:42,899
We understand that certain ages,

78
00:03:42,899 --> 00:03:46,059
that there's going to be crawling that takes place

79
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:48,179
and then there's going to be that crawling

80
00:03:48,179 --> 00:03:51,100
that turns to walking and there's going to be that talking

81
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:55,179
and the little words and oftentimes the first word being

82
00:03:55,179 --> 00:03:56,740
not mommy, but daddy.

83
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,940
And it's so often that mothers are,

84
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:01,899
I spend all day with you and you say daddy first.

85
00:04:01,899 --> 00:04:06,339
And the reality is that there's some milestones, right?

86
00:04:06,339 --> 00:04:10,139
We understand that physically, in physical growth.

87
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,619
As we look at the Word of God,

88
00:04:13,619 --> 00:04:17,059
we find that God has given us within His Word

89
00:04:17,059 --> 00:04:19,619
that there's to be evidence of spiritual growth

90
00:04:19,619 --> 00:04:21,380
and development as well.

91
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:25,019
We find that the Bible tells us in 1 Peter 2,

92
00:04:25,019 --> 00:04:29,239
as newborn babes desire the sincere milk of the Word,

93
00:04:29,239 --> 00:04:32,339
that ye may grow thereby.

94
00:04:32,339 --> 00:04:36,100
Just as there would be reason for concern of a parent

95
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:38,920
of a child that is not developing,

96
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:41,579
an equal amount of concern should be evidenced

97
00:04:41,579 --> 00:04:45,440
in the life of a believer where there's no growth.

98
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:49,720
We should not be content with nominal Christianity.

99
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:53,000
We should not be content with stagnated growth.

100
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,200
We should not be content with being worldly.

101
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:57,160
Amen?

102
00:04:57,160 --> 00:05:00,380
The reality is there should be evidence of growth.

103
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:06,320
So often, we would like to examine someone else's life.

104
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,600
I said to someone yesterday,

105
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:12,200
the reality is that you would prefer to evaluate my life

106
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:15,320
and I would prefer to evaluate your life.

107
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:19,839
Because the reality is that that process of self-examination

108
00:05:19,839 --> 00:05:21,880
is a challenging process.

109
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,600
Requires humility.

110
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,040
Requires honesty.

111
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:29,119
In 1 Corinthians 11, the passage of Scripture

112
00:05:29,119 --> 00:05:31,959
that we often use as we would observe the Lord's Supper,

113
00:05:31,959 --> 00:05:33,799
the Word of God tells us there,

114
00:05:33,799 --> 00:05:38,359
let a man examine himself.

115
00:05:38,359 --> 00:05:40,040
This morning, the title, as you've seen

116
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,279
in the bulletin already,

117
00:05:41,279 --> 00:05:45,480
is examine your spiritual maturity.

118
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:47,179
Examine your spiritual maturity.

119
00:05:47,179 --> 00:05:49,519
Notice in verse number 12 of 1 John 2,

120
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,600
the Bible says this,

121
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,320
I write unto you little children

122
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:57,279
because your sins are forgiven you for his namesake.

123
00:05:57,279 --> 00:05:58,519
I write unto you fathers

124
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:01,119
because you have known him that is from the beginning.

125
00:06:01,119 --> 00:06:02,519
I write unto you young men

126
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:04,880
because you have overcome the wicked one.

127
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,519
I write unto you little children

128
00:06:06,519 --> 00:06:08,359
because you have known the father.

129
00:06:08,359 --> 00:06:09,799
I have written unto you fathers

130
00:06:09,799 --> 00:06:12,119
because you have known him that is from the beginning.

131
00:06:12,119 --> 00:06:13,640
I have written unto you young men

132
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,799
because you are strong

133
00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:17,000
and the Word of God abideth in you

134
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,760
and you have overcome the wicked one.

135
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:23,559
These three addresses that are made,

136
00:06:23,559 --> 00:06:26,839
little children, fathers, and young men.

137
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:29,000
Again, as I mentioned a moment ago,

138
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,640
I believe that they're representative

139
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:34,200
of that spiritual growth and maturity

140
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,260
that we find in our Christian life.

141
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:37,859
And this morning, we're just gonna look

142
00:06:37,859 --> 00:06:39,359
at these three groups of people

143
00:06:39,359 --> 00:06:41,239
and see what it is that the Apostle John

144
00:06:41,239 --> 00:06:43,500
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God

145
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,640
says to these individuals.

146
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,559
If you're taking notes,

147
00:06:46,559 --> 00:06:48,959
the first group that we'll mention is the little children.

148
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:51,640
We find them referenced in verse number 12

149
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,239
and again in verse number 13.

150
00:06:53,239 --> 00:06:55,980
And we find that these little children are addressed.

151
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:59,279
And I would find that as we look at verse 12 and 13,

152
00:06:59,279 --> 00:07:00,600
that there are two statements

153
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,679
that are given about this group.

154
00:07:02,679 --> 00:07:04,000
I would refer to them,

155
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,480
John uses the terminology little children.

156
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:09,200
And I think a phrase that many of us are familiar with

157
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,239
would be babes in Christ, new believers.

158
00:07:13,239 --> 00:07:16,040
And notice what he says of these new believers

159
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,239
in verse number 12.

160
00:07:17,239 --> 00:07:19,200
He says, I write unto you little children,

161
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:23,160
notice this because your sins are forgiven you

162
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,359
for his namesake.

163
00:07:24,359 --> 00:07:26,399
Isn't that wonderful?

164
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:29,640
When you think about the reality of a new believer

165
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,899
and you think about your own life,

166
00:07:30,899 --> 00:07:33,399
when you first trusted Jesus Christ

167
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:34,899
as your personal savior,

168
00:07:34,899 --> 00:07:38,000
I would readily acknowledge and admit to you this morning

169
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,239
that I knew far less then than I do now.

170
00:07:42,559 --> 00:07:43,519
But I knew this thing,

171
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:45,339
I knew that I had been forgiven.

172
00:07:46,559 --> 00:07:51,559
I knew that Jesus Christ had forgiven me of my sins

173
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:55,179
and it was not because I deserved it,

174
00:07:55,179 --> 00:07:58,720
as he says here for his namesake,

175
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,619
because of his abundant grace,

176
00:08:01,619 --> 00:08:04,799
because of him being rich in mercy,

177
00:08:04,799 --> 00:08:07,959
because he is a God who is ready to pardon

178
00:08:08,799 --> 00:08:09,640
and ready to forgive,

179
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:12,600
because he said whosoever shall call upon the name

180
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:16,079
of the Lord shall be saved.

181
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:18,600
I didn't understand a lot of theological terms

182
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,320
that I understand today.

183
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:23,119
I did not understand a lot of the attributes of God

184
00:08:23,119 --> 00:08:24,899
that I understand today.

185
00:08:24,899 --> 00:08:27,359
But I understood some important truth

186
00:08:27,359 --> 00:08:30,119
and I understood that I was a sinner in need of a savior.

187
00:08:30,119 --> 00:08:32,640
And I understood that he was the only savior

188
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:35,859
and I understood that he died for me on that cruel cross.

189
00:08:35,859 --> 00:08:38,419
We sang this morning about the old rugged cross

190
00:08:38,419 --> 00:08:41,099
and how thankful I am that Jesus Christ,

191
00:08:41,099 --> 00:08:43,940
God in flesh, went to that cruel cross.

192
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,299
He suffered, he bled and he died.

193
00:08:46,299 --> 00:08:49,099
And I recognized that he did it for me.

194
00:08:50,820 --> 00:08:55,419
And he rose in victory, conquering sin, death and the grave

195
00:08:55,419 --> 00:08:59,659
and he offered me forgiveness because he loved me.

196
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:03,419
I didn't comprehend all of it.

197
00:09:03,419 --> 00:09:05,140
But man, I understood that I was a sinner

198
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:06,359
and he is the savior.

199
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:11,039
And little children, babes in Christ,

200
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:14,140
at that moment of salvation, one thing that we know,

201
00:09:14,140 --> 00:09:19,140
one thing that we understand is that our sins are forgiven.

202
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,179
You know, there's only one way to be forgiven

203
00:09:21,179 --> 00:09:24,179
and that's through the blood of Jesus Christ.

204
00:09:24,179 --> 00:09:27,780
The Bible tells us in Colossians chapter number one

205
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:31,219
and verse number 14, a precious verse of scripture

206
00:09:31,219 --> 00:09:33,840
with regard to the subject of being forgiven.

207
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,400
It says, in whom we have redemption through his blood,

208
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:39,900
even the forgiveness of sins.

209
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,479
Unfortunately, there are many people today

210
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:45,119
that do not know the truth of forgiveness.

211
00:09:45,119 --> 00:09:47,500
They do not know what it means to be forgiven.

212
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:50,400
They cannot stand and rejoice in the fact

213
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,940
that they have been forgiven.

214
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:56,000
But the little children, the babes in Christ

215
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,559
that John is addressing here,

216
00:09:58,559 --> 00:10:01,080
they know that their sins are forgiven.

217
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:04,760
Our sins are forgiven for His namesake,

218
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:07,480
because of His grace and because of His mercy,

219
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:11,340
because of His great love wherewith He loved us.

220
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:12,920
Our sins are forgiven.

221
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:15,840
Notice what He says to this same group of people

222
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,520
at the end of verse 13.

223
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,420
He says this,

224
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:20,800
I write unto you little children,

225
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:21,640
notice this,

226
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:24,280
because you have known the Father.

227
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,720
I believe that there's an obvious difference

228
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,720
between the statement that is made here

229
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:31,060
of these little children at the end of verse 13

230
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:33,440
and that which will be said to the fathers

231
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,740
as we get to here in just a few moments.

232
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:37,460
But we find that as He would refer

233
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:39,340
to these little children that begin

234
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:41,820
with the knowledge that they're forgiven,

235
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:45,260
I also find that I begin to understand this truth

236
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:47,140
as a babe in Christ,

237
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:48,380
as a little child,

238
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:50,900
that I am His Son and He is my Father.

239
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:56,480
I find that He's my Heavenly Father,

240
00:10:56,480 --> 00:11:00,180
that I've been adopted into the family of God.

241
00:11:00,180 --> 00:11:01,620
Isn't that wonderful?

242
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:03,580
And you begin to understand that again,

243
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,880
the layers continue to peel off

244
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:08,180
and you find the depth of the truth

245
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:10,800
that you find as just a little child

246
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:12,740
that now someone would say to you

247
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,940
as I've said to people over my ministry

248
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,920
and as someone said to me,

249
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:19,260
when I trust that Christ is my Savior

250
00:11:19,260 --> 00:11:21,340
and I understood that I was forgiven

251
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,900
and they said something like this,

252
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:25,300
now God is your Father.

253
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:27,580
Man, that's precious.

254
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,100
Notice what the Word of God says

255
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:31,060
in Galatians chapter number four.

256
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:33,740
Take a moment and turn there if you will.

257
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:36,260
In Galatians chapter number four

258
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:38,080
in verses five and six,

259
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,740
and what great truth that is given to us

260
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:43,300
with regard to this relationship.

261
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,860
Remember, we've often spoken about fellowship

262
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:47,220
in the book of 1 John,

263
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,780
and fellowship is important

264
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:51,380
and I'm thankful that we can have fellowship with God,

265
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:55,460
but that fellowship is on the basis of the relationship.

266
00:11:55,460 --> 00:11:57,280
We said that in our very first message.

267
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:59,060
You cannot have fellowship,

268
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,380
you cannot walk in the light

269
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:04,220
if you do not have relationship.

270
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:07,620
And in order to have fellowship with Christ,

271
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:09,420
you must have relationship

272
00:12:09,420 --> 00:12:11,380
and understanding that relationship

273
00:12:11,380 --> 00:12:13,780
includes the fact that I've been forgiven

274
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:17,240
but that he's my Father and I'm his son, I'm his child.

275
00:12:18,140 --> 00:12:20,100
In Galatians chapter number four,

276
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:23,060
the Bible begins in verse number four by saying,

277
00:12:23,060 --> 00:12:26,060
but when the fullness of the time was come,

278
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:29,380
God sent forth his Son made of a woman,

279
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:31,620
made under the law, for what purpose?

280
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,740
To redeem them that were under the law.

281
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:35,260
How were we redeemed?

282
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:36,740
Through the blood of Christ.

283
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:40,000
That's that forgiveness that he spoke of in Colossians one

284
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,260
that we might receive,

285
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:45,280
notice what he says, the adoption of sons.

286
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,620
Notice this in verse number six,

287
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:51,020
and because ye are sons,

288
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,420
God hath sent forth the spirit of his Son

289
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:57,940
into your hearts crying, Abba, Father.

290
00:12:57,940 --> 00:13:02,940
You know what the most accurate English translation

291
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:06,980
that we would use for that word Abba is daddy.

292
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:09,100
Now think about that.

293
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:11,620
God is my Father.

294
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:17,380
I have this relationship with him.

295
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:19,900
And as a little child,

296
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:22,420
understanding spiritually speaking

297
00:13:22,420 --> 00:13:24,740
is the emphasis here in the book of 1 John,

298
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,060
he's writing to these babes in Christ.

299
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:30,380
Let me say this, this is where we all begin.

300
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:32,660
You must begin as a little child, right?

301
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:35,100
You must be born again.

302
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,660
And at that moment of being born again,

303
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:39,620
that's when we understand that our sins are forgiven

304
00:13:39,620 --> 00:13:41,940
and we understand that he's my Father

305
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:46,940
and we all begin there, but we ought not stay there.

306
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:47,860
Amen?

307
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:50,460
We begin as little children physically,

308
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:52,220
but we grow and we develop

309
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:55,340
and we understand that process of physical growth

310
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:59,700
in such as the case spiritually that we are born again

311
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:02,980
and we're babes in Christ, we're little children

312
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:05,860
with a limited amount of knowledge and understanding,

313
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:10,020
but we understand these two profound truths.

314
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:13,100
I'm forgiven and he's my Father.

315
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,620
And how precious that is.

316
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:20,620
The Old Testament gives us a wonderful example of this

317
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,860
in the life of David,

318
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:27,140
when he desires to show kindness into the house of Saul

319
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,740
for the sake of Jonathan,

320
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:31,820
and he makes inquiry whether there were any that remained

321
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:33,940
and he finds out about this one,

322
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:37,020
a son of Jonathan, Mephibosheth.

323
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:41,860
He was lame, he had nothing to offer.

324
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,980
He was lame because at the time

325
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:47,420
in which he was being cared for,

326
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:50,260
news came that Saul and Jonathan and the others

327
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:51,940
were defeated by the Philistines

328
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:55,260
and the nurse that was caring for him tried to hurry out

329
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,740
and there was a fall and he was lame.

330
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:00,900
And David says, bring him to me.

331
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,420
He was down in Lodabar.

332
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:05,540
And David says, bring him to me and he comes

333
00:15:05,540 --> 00:15:08,340
and no doubt he's fearful and uncertain

334
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:10,300
as to the meeting with the king

335
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:13,740
and understanding some of the customs

336
00:15:13,740 --> 00:15:16,940
with dealing with prior family

337
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:18,820
of those that reigned before you.

338
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:22,260
And he says, what do you want with a dead dog such as I?

339
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:26,940
And David says, you're gonna be as one of the king's sons.

340
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:28,420
You're gonna sit at my table.

341
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:33,340
And he gave him land and he gave him servants

342
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:35,460
and he gave them provision.

343
00:15:35,460 --> 00:15:38,140
And he said, but Mephibosheth, you're gonna sit at my table

344
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:40,580
as one of the king's sons.

345
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:42,300
And to understand that salvation,

346
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:45,740
that I've been forgiven and he's my father.

347
00:15:45,740 --> 00:15:49,100
We all begin there, but we ought not stay there.

348
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:53,900
We ought to be mindful of these foundational truths.

349
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:56,860
The foundation is what we build upon.

350
00:15:56,860 --> 00:15:58,780
And the foundation is so important

351
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:00,940
that we understand our security in Christ

352
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:03,620
and that relationship that we have with Christ

353
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:07,100
that he is my father and I am his child.

354
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:10,740
I mentioned already in 1 Peter 2,

355
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:13,100
that we're to grow as newborn babes desire

356
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:16,300
the sincere milk of the word that you may grow thereby.

357
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,140
And that's where we kind of continue here

358
00:16:18,140 --> 00:16:19,900
through this passage of scripture.

359
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,460
I understand that the next group

360
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:23,440
that is mentioned in verse 13 is fathers,

361
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,020
but for sake of the message this morning,

362
00:16:26,020 --> 00:16:29,540
I'm going to deal with the young men for our second point.

363
00:16:29,540 --> 00:16:32,340
He writes to these young men in verse 13.

364
00:16:32,340 --> 00:16:33,760
And again, in verse number 14,

365
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:36,520
it's the second group of people that are identified.

366
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,800
And we find that there are three statements

367
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,200
that are given about this group of believers.

368
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,840
I would say that these believers are growing and maturing.

369
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:47,880
These believers are going further with Christ.

370
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,160
They're walking with Christ.

371
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:51,560
They're learning of him and they're growing

372
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:54,760
and developing in their Christian life.

373
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,320
We find that the Bible says in verse number 13,

374
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,480
I write unto you fathers because you have known him

375
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,360
that is from the beginning,

376
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:05,040
but notice he then says, I write unto you young men.

377
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:05,920
Why?

378
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:08,040
Number one, the first statement that is given

379
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,040
in verse number 13,

380
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:12,920
because you have overcome the wicked one.

381
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,200
You know what you begin to find out

382
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,360
as you walk with Christ, you have an enemy.

383
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,040
That's what you find out, right?

384
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:22,920
When I got saved, I knew that my sins were forgiven.

385
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:25,760
When I got saved, I knew he was my father.

386
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:27,480
And then as I begin to walk with Christ,

387
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,720
I find out that I have an adversary.

388
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,180
I have an enemy, the devil,

389
00:17:31,180 --> 00:17:34,560
who wants to devour me and destroy me.

390
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:37,280
And we learn that, we learn the importance

391
00:17:37,280 --> 00:17:39,440
of putting on the whole armor of God.

392
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:43,040
We learn that the Christian life, as Tozer said,

393
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:46,200
is more adequately and appropriately described

394
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:49,480
as being a battleground, not a playground.

395
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:54,080
We're engaged in spiritual warfare.

396
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:58,040
I know that our society wants to tell us

397
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:01,840
that we're dealing with all of these various aspects

398
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:06,160
of warfare that is social and so on and so forth,

399
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:09,600
but we are dealing with spiritual warfare.

400
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,640
That's what we're dealing with in our society.

401
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:16,760
We find that as a believer, as we grow,

402
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,600
as we're growing and maturing,

403
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,000
we find that we are engaged in spiritual warfare.

404
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,320
I think of the great truth that God gives us

405
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,680
in 1 Peter chapter number five,

406
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,240
when Peter, who had experienced,

407
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,200
remember, the Lord Jesus Christ said,

408
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:36,640
Peter, Satan hath desired to have you,

409
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,960
that he may sift you as wheat.

410
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:42,799
But he says this, I have prayed for thee.

411
00:18:42,799 --> 00:18:43,720
Isn't that sweet?

412
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,239
Isn't that precious?

413
00:18:45,239 --> 00:18:47,520
Jesus says, Peter, I've prayed for thee

414
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,200
that thy faith fail not.

415
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:54,440
When thou art converted, strengthen thy brethren.

416
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:58,760
And God used Peter to be a great pillar in the early church,

417
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,960
and he preached on the day of Pentecost,

418
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:04,640
and he was faithful in delivering the gospel message.

419
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:07,840
He stood in boldness before the religious leaders,

420
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:11,840
and he proclaimed the truth of the gospel.

421
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:13,880
And then God would use him as the human penman

422
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:16,200
for those two books, 1 and 2 Peter.

423
00:19:17,119 --> 00:19:19,040
And he says in the fifth chapter,

424
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:22,200
be sober, be vigilant,

425
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,760
because your adversary, the devil,

426
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:26,840
is a warring lion, walketh about seeking

427
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,360
whom he may devour.

428
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,440
Who better to write that under the inspiration

429
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:35,360
of the Holy Spirit of God than Peter?

430
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:38,679
We know that it's God's word, but God used man.

431
00:19:38,679 --> 00:19:43,679
And Peter understood that sifting as wheat

432
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,920
that Jesus spoke of before his crucifixion.

433
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:51,160
Peter understood the adversity and the enemy,

434
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,799
the opposition that he faced.

435
00:19:53,119 --> 00:19:57,400
We find that as growing and maturing believers,

436
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,320
we are engaged in spiritual warfare.

437
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:01,200
But I want you to notice what he says.

438
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:04,660
that you have overcome the wicked one.

439
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:06,340
Aren't you thankful for the truth?

440
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:11,340
Romans 8, we are more than conquerors through Christ.

441
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:15,380
I am thankful, as Curtis Hudson used to regularly sing

442
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:18,800
at the end of messages, I am on the winning side.

443
00:20:19,940 --> 00:20:23,220
But thanks be to God, which giveth us the victory

444
00:20:23,220 --> 00:20:25,340
through our Lord Jesus Christ.

445
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:29,580
We find that in 1 Corinthians 15 and verse number 57.

446
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:33,140
He says you have overcome the wicked one.

447
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:35,900
More insight is given to us in verse number 14

448
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:38,220
with regard to the spiritual warfare

449
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:40,860
and to this victory that had been experienced.

450
00:20:40,860 --> 00:20:43,260
Notice in verse 14, he says I have written unto you

451
00:20:43,260 --> 00:20:44,740
fathers because you have known him

452
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:45,580
that is from the beginning.

453
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:48,180
Notice again, I have written unto you young men.

454
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:49,020
Why?

455
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,060
Because you are strong.

456
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:55,260
He's not referring to physical strength.

457
00:20:55,260 --> 00:21:00,020
No doubt we could understand that the analogy

458
00:21:00,020 --> 00:21:03,620
that is used, little children and young men and fathers

459
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:06,460
and you could think about the physical aspect

460
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:09,620
of the strength of young men, but this is a spiritual book

461
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:11,500
and he's dealing with spiritual truth

462
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:15,260
and the reality is that he's speaking of a spiritual strength

463
00:21:15,260 --> 00:21:18,300
that these young men exhibited during this

464
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:21,180
spiritual warfare, this battle.

465
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:22,900
He says you are strong.

466
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,700
Where does this strength come from?

467
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:26,500
What is the source of the strength?

468
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:29,060
I'm glad that we do not need to sit around

469
00:21:29,060 --> 00:21:31,740
and figure out and try to come up with ideas

470
00:21:31,740 --> 00:21:34,580
of where the strength originated for the next phrase says

471
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:37,700
in the word of God abideth in you.

472
00:21:38,620 --> 00:21:40,700
That's where the strength comes from.

473
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:44,860
That's where we have that spiritual strength

474
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:47,660
that God is speaking of of these young men

475
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:49,900
who have overcome the wicked one.

476
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,100
These young men that have been victorious,

477
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,420
he says again at the end of verse number 14

478
00:21:55,140 --> 00:21:57,340
and ye have overcome the wicked one.

479
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:04,300
The strength is because the word of God abideth in you.

480
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:09,780
How important that we pause and just take a moment

481
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:12,860
to consider the importance of being strengthened

482
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:14,620
in the inner man.

483
00:22:14,620 --> 00:22:17,900
Paul as he prays for the believers in Ephesus,

484
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:21,540
Paul as he speaks about the importance of walking

485
00:22:21,540 --> 00:22:24,860
in the spirit and not fulfilling the lust of the flesh

486
00:22:24,860 --> 00:22:27,940
and seeks to encourage those that God would give them

487
00:22:27,940 --> 00:22:29,820
the opportunity to minister to,

488
00:22:29,820 --> 00:22:31,820
he speaks and he prays for them

489
00:22:31,820 --> 00:22:35,180
that they would be strengthened in the inner man.

490
00:22:36,340 --> 00:22:38,420
He's not speaking about physical strength.

491
00:22:40,660 --> 00:22:44,340
Paul was a man that faced great trial and difficulty.

492
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:45,980
He goes on missionary journeys

493
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:48,780
and he faces opposition at every turn.

494
00:22:48,780 --> 00:22:51,620
His body is beaten and worn and torn

495
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:53,700
and the physical strength fails

496
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:56,860
but he's strengthened in his inner man.

497
00:22:57,820 --> 00:23:00,460
You can read of those that have gone before us,

498
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:02,380
those that were martyred for their faith,

499
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:05,100
those that suffered great adversity

500
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,860
for preaching and teaching this precious book,

501
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:09,780
the word of God and you can see how that

502
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:14,780
their physical bodies were beaten and worn down

503
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:16,820
but they had a strength.

504
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:21,300
They had a strength that was noticeable.

505
00:23:22,420 --> 00:23:25,060
A strength that was a result

506
00:23:25,060 --> 00:23:28,740
of the word of God abiding in them.

507
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,140
Turn over just for a moment, if you will,

508
00:23:30,140 --> 00:23:34,060
to the book of 2 Corinthians in the fourth chapter.

509
00:23:34,060 --> 00:23:36,580
We'll be mindful of this truth as we turn there

510
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:38,860
that the Lord Jesus Christ in the book of Matthew,

511
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:39,940
again in the book of Luke,

512
00:23:39,940 --> 00:23:42,180
the record is given to us with regard

513
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:44,300
to the temptation in the wilderness

514
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:46,100
and he gives us a great pattern

515
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:48,300
where he says it is written.

516
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:50,940
How did he overcome the evil one?

517
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:53,860
When the tempter comes and seeks to tempt him,

518
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,940
he overcomes by saying it is written

519
00:23:56,940 --> 00:24:00,180
and we too take and understand from that truth

520
00:24:00,180 --> 00:24:03,540
of Matthew and Luke that we must abide

521
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:06,940
in the word of God and the word of God must abide in us.

522
00:24:06,940 --> 00:24:09,900
Someone said this, greater than footprints on the moon

523
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:13,740
are thumbprints in the Bible and I like that.

524
00:24:14,380 --> 00:24:17,500
We need to get this word into us.

525
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,100
We need to know it and it ought to be said of us

526
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:23,260
that the word of God abideth in you

527
00:24:23,260 --> 00:24:25,460
that we're skillful with the word of God.

528
00:24:25,460 --> 00:24:27,340
Notice in 2 Corinthians chapter number four

529
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:28,500
and verse number one,

530
