we'd be honest with God, honest with ourselves, not to think of ourselves more highly than

781
00:39:22,359 --> 00:39:31,320
we ought, and to truly say, Lord, I just want to know You in a deep, intimate way.

782
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:36,600
I'm so thankful that You're my Father, but I want to know more about my Father.

783
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:37,600
Amen?

784
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:41,799
I want to know as much as I can possibly know about Him.

785
00:39:41,799 --> 00:39:44,640
And I'm going to find that in this book.

786
00:39:44,679 --> 00:39:48,919
John says, I'm writing unto you, and here's my purpose.

787
00:39:48,919 --> 00:39:53,919
He's already given us some purposes, so I should say, here my purpose is.

788
00:39:53,919 --> 00:39:57,400
And this morning, we have time to examine and evaluate.

789
00:39:57,400 --> 00:40:01,239
Father, we love You.

790
00:40:01,239 --> 00:40:08,359
thankful for salvation, those little children that are referred to, knowing that their sins

791
00:40:08,359 --> 00:40:17,479
are forgiven, finding that they've been adopted into the family of God.

792
00:40:17,479 --> 00:40:20,759
We all start there.

793
00:40:20,759 --> 00:40:25,959
Perhaps there'd be one this morning that, as they would honestly evaluate their lives,

794
00:40:25,959 --> 00:40:29,979
they'd say, I've never been saved, I've never been born again.

795
00:40:29,979 --> 00:40:35,759
I don't know that my sins are forgiven.

796
00:40:35,759 --> 00:40:40,339
I don't know that I'm His child.

797
00:40:40,339 --> 00:40:44,739
Could I extend an invitation to you this morning to get that settled?

798
00:40:44,739 --> 00:40:49,299
The Word of God says that, behold, today is the day of salvation.

799
00:40:49,299 --> 00:40:56,539
It'd be our prayer that before you would leave this place or tune off of live stream, that

800
00:40:56,539 --> 00:41:00,419
you would know with certainty that heaven is your home.

801
00:41:00,419 --> 00:41:11,819
To the believer this morning, the one who knows they're forgiven, knows that you're

802
00:41:11,819 --> 00:41:17,779
our Father, I pray that you'd help us to examine and evaluate our lives.

803
00:41:17,779 --> 00:41:22,179
Is the Word of God abiding in us?

804
00:41:22,179 --> 00:41:23,619
Are we strong spiritually?

805
00:41:23,699 --> 00:41:27,899
Are we overcoming the enemy?

806
00:41:27,899 --> 00:41:31,779
Are we victorious?

807
00:41:31,779 --> 00:41:34,259
Do we know You?

808
00:41:34,259 --> 00:41:38,659
Is that our lifelong pursuit?

809
00:41:38,659 --> 00:41:49,619
Do we go to Your Word with the same level of desire that is mentioned in Psalm 42, pursuing

810
00:41:49,619 --> 00:41:54,659
You, desiring to know You?

811
00:41:54,659 --> 00:42:05,139
Help us, Lord, to have evidenced in our lives spiritual growth, that we would grow in grace

812
00:42:05,139 --> 00:42:10,139
and knowledge of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ.

813
00:42:10,139 --> 00:42:16,219
I pray that You'd move and work as only You can as we have a time of invitation that Your

814
00:42:16,219 --> 00:42:18,619
people, Lord, would respond.

815
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:22,419
And we'll give You the honor and glory for the work that You'll do.

816
00:42:22,419 --> 00:42:26,779
For it's in Christ's name we pray, would You stand with me?

817
00:42:26,779 --> 00:42:29,579
Heads are bowed, eyes are closed, no one looking around.

818
00:42:29,579 --> 00:42:36,219
As we end our services, we seek to give You an opportunity to respond.

819
00:42:36,219 --> 00:42:40,499
Kimberly will play quietly on the piano, and as she does, the altar's open.

820
00:42:40,499 --> 00:42:43,859
Maybe you want to come and thank Him.

821
00:42:43,859 --> 00:42:48,979
Maybe you want to come and ask Him to search you and help you in your journey, truly knowing

822
00:42:48,979 --> 00:42:57,759
Him in a deep, abiding relationship and fellowship with Him, having that peace and that joy.

823
00:42:57,759 --> 00:42:59,579
As Kimberly plays, the altar is open.

